{
  "stem": "4967.3",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I, personally, myself, thought they take us somewhere else, but they took her to the hospital.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And we were four days in the yard of the police station with no food, water [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And-- and the ghetto was blowing up to pieces.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Smoke, fire, terribly.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And they took out all the people from the ghetto through the main gate to-- and they had to march six kilometers to a railway siding.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] The police told us, they're marching and they were transported somewhere by rail.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And-- and the third day, the Germans came to us, and they told us we must march three in a row, and we marched to the siding.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And we come to the siding, and there were trains, cattle cars waiting for us.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "Cattle trains, whatever you call it, [NON-ENGLISH], and we were pushed into those cattle trains.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And the ghetto was blowing up to pieces.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "Nobody remained there.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "People were in hideouts.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "If we wouldn't-- If we wouldn't go out for fresh air from our hideout, we would've most likely blown up to pieces, because there was dynamite in this particular windowsill and it would've blown up.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And this was the end of the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "People marched to the trains, and they were transported to Poland and to Germany.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
